Definition.WordDefinition: Prenatal \Pre*na"tal\, a. Being or happening before birth. [1913 Webster]
prenatal adj : occurring or existing before birth; "the prenatal period"; "antenatal care" [syn: {antenatal}, {antepartum}] [ant: {perinatal}, {postnatal}]
